**Creating participant with TypeLookup service enabled:**
```cpp
using namespace eprosima::fastdds::dds;

DomainParticipantQos pqos;
pqos.name("MyParticipant");

// Enable TypeLookup client (to discover remote types)
pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_client = true;
// Enable TypeLookup server (to serve our types to others)
pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_server = false;

DomainParticipant* participant =
    DomainParticipantFactory::get_instance()->create_participant(
        0,              // domain_id
        pqos,           // QoS
        &listener,      // DomainParticipantListener*
        StatusMask::none());
```

The `DomainParticipantFactory` is a singleton accessed via `get_instance()`. The `create_participant()` method signature:
```cpp
DomainParticipant* create_participant(
    DomainId_t domain_id,
    const DomainParticipantQos& qos,
    DomainParticipantListener* listener = nullptr,
    const StatusMask& mask = StatusMask::all());
```

**TypeLookup config fields:**
- `pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_client` -- set `true` on subscribers to discover remote types
- `pqos.wire_protocol().builtin.typelookup_config.use_server` -- set `true` on publishers to serve type info

