### 3. DynamicType Resolution from TypeObject

**Headers:**
```cpp
#include <fastdds/dds/domain/DomainParticipantFactory.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/type_representation/TypeObject.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/type_representation/ITypeObjectRegistry.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/dynamic_types/DynamicTypeBuilderFactory.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/dynamic_types/DynamicTypeBuilder.hpp>
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/dynamic_types/DynamicType.hpp>
```

**Getting TypeObject from TypeObjectRegistry:**

The `ITypeObjectRegistry` interface is accessed via the `DomainParticipantFactory` singleton:

```cpp
xtypes::TypeObject remote_type_object;

// Get TypeIdentifier from discovery info
const auto& type_id = info.type_information
    .type_information.complete().typeid_with_size().type_id();

if (RETCODE_OK != DomainParticipantFactory::get_instance()
        ->type_object_registry().get_type_object(type_id, remote_type_object))
{
    // Error: type not found in registry
    return;
}
```

**ITypeObjectRegistry key methods:**

| Method | Signature |
|--------|-----------|
| `get_type_object` | `ReturnCode_t get_type_object(const TypeIdentifier& type_identifier, TypeObject& type_object)` |
| `get_type_identifiers` | `ReturnCode_t get_type_identifiers(const std::string& type_name, TypeIdentifierPair& type_identifiers)` |
| `get_type_objects` | `ReturnCode_t get_type_objects(const std::string& type_name, TypeObjectPair& type_objects)` |
| `get_type_information` | `ReturnCode_t get_type_information(const TypeIdentifierPair& type_ids, TypeInformation& type_information, bool with_dependencies = false)` |
| `register_type_object` | `ReturnCode_t register_type_object(const std::string& type_name, const CompleteTypeObject& complete_type_object, TypeIdentifierPair& type_ids)` |
| `register_typeobject_w_dynamic_type` | `ReturnCode_t register_typeobject_w_dynamic_type(const DynamicType::_ref_type& dynamic_type, TypeIdentifierPair& type_ids)` |

**Building DynamicType from TypeObject:**

```cpp
// DynamicTypeBuilderFactory::create_type_w_type_object signature:
// virtual traits<DynamicTypeBuilder>::ref_type create_type_w_type_object(
//     const xtypes::TypeObject& type_object) = 0;

DynamicType::_ref_type remote_type =
    DynamicTypeBuilderFactory::get_instance()->create_type_w_type_object(
        remote_type_object)->build();
```

**Checking type kind:**

`TypeKind` is defined as `uint8_t` in the xtypes detail header. Key constants:
```cpp
// From <fastdds/dds/xtypes/type_representation/detail/dds_xtypes_typeobject.hpp>
const uint8_t TK_NONE      = 0x00;
const uint8_t TK_STRUCTURE = 0x51;
```

You can check the kind of a `DynamicType`:
```cpp
// DynamicType::get_kind() returns TypeKind
if (remote_type->get_kind() == TK_STRUCTURE) {
    // It's a struct
}
```

You can also get the type name:
```cpp
ObjectName name = remote_type->get_name();  // returns ObjectName (string-like)
```

Sources: [ITypeObjectRegistry API (3.0.1)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/v3.0.1/fastdds/api_reference/dds_pim/xtypes/typeobjectregistry.html), [DynamicTypeBuilderFactory API (3.3)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/latest/fastdds/api_reference/dds_pim/xtypes/dynamictypebuilderfactory.html), [Serialization Utilities (3.4)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/latest/fastdds/xtypes/type_serializing.html), [Fast-DDS source code v3.4.0](https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-DDS/tree/v3.4.0)

