### 4. IDL Generation from DynamicType

**Header:**
```cpp
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/utils.hpp>
```

Confirmed from source tree: `include/fastdds/dds/xtypes/utils.hpp`

**Function signature:**
```cpp
namespace eprosima {
namespace fastdds {
namespace dds {

FASTDDS_EXPORTED_API ReturnCode_t idl_serialize(
    const DynamicType::_ref_type& dynamic_type,
    std::ostream& output) noexcept;

}}} // namespace
```

**Usage:**
```cpp
#include <fastdds/dds/xtypes/utils.hpp>
#include <sstream>

std::stringstream idl;
if (RETCODE_OK != idl_serialize(remote_type, idl))
{
    // Error
    return;
}
std::string idl_string = idl.str();
```

**Other functions in the same header:**
```cpp
// JSON serialization of DynamicData
enum class DynamicDataJsonFormat { OMG, EPROSIMA };

FASTDDS_EXPORTED_API ReturnCode_t json_serialize(
    const DynamicData::_ref_type& data,
    DynamicDataJsonFormat format,
    std::ostream& output) noexcept;

FASTDDS_EXPORTED_API ReturnCode_t json_deserialize(
    const std::string& input,
    const DynamicType::_ref_type& dynamic_type,
    DynamicDataJsonFormat format,
    DynamicData::_ref_type& data) noexcept;
```

**IDL serialization limitations:**
- Only supports builtin annotations: `@bit_bound`, `@extensibility`, `@key`, `@position`
- Values set to default are dismissed (e.g., `@bit_bound(32)` on Bitmask is omitted)
- Bitset with inheritance: derived bitsets merge with base bitset

Sources: [Serialization Utilities (3.4)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/latest/fastdds/xtypes/type_serializing.html), [Fast-DDS v3.4.0 utils.hpp source](https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-DDS/blob/v3.4.0/include/fastdds/dds/xtypes/utils.hpp)

