### 6. CDR Extraction (Serialize/Deserialize DynamicData)

**SerializedPayload_t structure** (from `<fastdds/rtps/common/SerializedPayload.hpp>`):
```cpp
struct SerializedPayload_t {
    uint16_t encapsulation;  // CDR_BE or CDR_LE
    uint32_t length;         // Actual data length
    octet* data;             // Pointer to raw CDR bytes
    uint32_t max_size;       // Allocated buffer size
    uint32_t pos;            // Current position
    // ...
};
```

**DynamicPubSubType serialize/deserialize methods:**
```cpp
// Serialize DynamicData to CDR payload
bool serialize(
    const void* const data,                       // DynamicData* cast to void*
    eprosima::fastdds::rtps::SerializedPayload_t& payload,
    fastdds::dds::DataRepresentationId_t data_representation) override;

// Deserialize CDR payload to DynamicData
bool deserialize(
    eprosima::fastdds::rtps::SerializedPayload_t& payload,
    void* data) override;                         // DynamicData* cast to void*

// Calculate serialized size
uint32_t calculate_serialized_size(
    const void* const data,
    DataRepresentationId_t data_representation) override;
```

**Reading DynamicData from DataReader and extracting CDR bytes:**
```cpp
// Create a DynamicPubSubType for serialization
DynamicPubSubType pub_sub_type(dyn_type);

// Read from DataReader
DynamicData::_ref_type data =
    DynamicDataFactory::get_instance()->create_data(dyn_type);
SampleInfo info;

while (RETCODE_OK == reader->take_next_sample(&data, &info))
{
    if (!info.valid_data) continue;

    // Serialize DynamicData to CDR bytes
    uint32_t size = pub_sub_type.calculate_serialized_size(
        &data, DataRepresentationId_t::XCDR2_DATA_REPRESENTATION);
    SerializedPayload_t payload(size);
    pub_sub_type.serialize(&data, payload,
        DataRepresentationId_t::XCDR2_DATA_REPRESENTATION);

    // payload.data now points to CDR bytes, payload.length is the size
    // Copy to vector:
    std::vector<uint8_t> cdr_bytes(payload.data, payload.data + payload.length);
}
```

**SampleInfo structure:**
```cpp
struct SampleInfo {
    SampleStateKind sample_state;           // READ or NOT_READ
    ViewStateKind view_state;               // NEW or NOT_NEW
    InstanceStateKind instance_state;       // ALIVE, NOT_ALIVE_DISPOSED, NOT_ALIVE_NO_WRITERS
    uint32_t disposed_generation_count;
    uint32_t no_writers_generation_count;
    uint32_t sample_rank;
    uint32_t generation_rank;
    uint32_t absolute_generation_rank;
    Time_t source_timestamp;                // <-- Publisher's timestamp
    InstanceHandle_t instance_handle;
    InstanceHandle_t publication_handle;
    bool valid_data;
    SampleIdentity sample_identity;
    SampleIdentity related_sample_identity;
};
```

**Time_t structure:**
```cpp
struct Time_t {
    int32_t seconds;    // Seconds since epoch
    uint32_t nanosec;   // Nanoseconds component
};
```

**Accessing source timestamp:**
```cpp
uint64_t timestamp_ns = static_cast<uint64_t>(info.source_timestamp.seconds) * 1000000000ULL
                       + info.source_timestamp.nanosec;
```

Sources: [SampleInfo (3.4)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/latest/fastdds/dds_layer/subscriber/sampleInfo/sampleInfo.html), [Accessing received data (3.4)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/latest/fastdds/dds_layer/subscriber/dataReader/readingData.html), [SerializedPayload_t API (3.1)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/3.1.x/fastdds/api_reference/rtps/common/SerializedPayload/SerializedPayload_t.html)

---

### 7. Conan CMake Target Names for fast-dds/3.4.0

**Confirmed from the Conan Center recipe** (`conan-center-index/recipes/fast-dds/all/conanfile.py`):

For **Fast DDS >= 3.0.0** (including 3.4.0):

| Package | `find_package()` name | `target_link_libraries()` target |
|---------|----------------------|----------------------------------|
| Fast-DDS | `find_package(fastdds 3 REQUIRED)` | `fastdds` |
| Fast-CDR | `find_package(fastcdr 2 REQUIRED)` | `fastcdr` |

The Conan recipe sets:
```python
# For v3.x:
self.cpp_info.set_property("cmake_file_name", "fastdds")
self.cpp_info.set_property("cmake_target_name", "fastdds")
self.cpp_info.libs = ["fastdds"]
```

**Important:** The CMake targets are **NOT namespaced** in the Fast-DDS project. They are plain `fastdds` and `fastcdr` (not `fastdds::fastdds` or `fastcdr::fastcdr`). This is confirmed by the official simple app example:

```cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.20)
project(DDSHelloWorld)

if(NOT fastcdr_FOUND)
    find_package(fastcdr 2 REQUIRED)
endif()

if(NOT fastdds_FOUND)
    find_package(fastdds 3 REQUIRED)
endif()

add_executable(my_app src/main.cpp)
target_link_libraries(my_app fastdds fastcdr)
```

**Fast-CDR dependency for fast-dds 3.4.0:** `fast-cdr/2.3.0` (Conan package name is `fast-cdr`, but CMake find name is `fastcdr`).

**Other transitive dependencies** from Conan:
- `asio/1.29.0`
- `tinyxml2/10.0.0`
- `foonathan-memory/0.7.3`

Sources: [Conan Center fast-dds recipe](https://conan.io/center/recipes/fast-dds), [Simple app tutorial (3.4)](https://fast-dds.docs.eprosima.com/en/3.4.x/fastdds/getting_started/simple_app/simple_app.html), [Conan Center fast-dds conanfile.py](https://github.com/conan-io/conan-center-index/blob/master/recipes/fast-dds/all/conanfile.py)

---

